## Cross-Platform Requirements (iOS + Android)

FitRealm ships on both platforms simultaneously. React Native handles most of the abstraction, but these areas require platform-specific attention. Claude Code must test both platforms for every feature.

### Platform-Specific Libraries

| Feature | iOS | Android | Abstraction Layer |
|---|---|---|---|
| Health Data | Apple HealthKit | Google Health Connect | `react-native-health` (wraps both) |
| Location (foreground) | Core Location | Fused Location Provider | `react-native-background-geolocation` (handles both) |
| Location (background) | Core Location + "When In Use" | ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION + foreground service | Same library, different permissions |
| In-App Purchases | StoreKit 2 | Google Play Billing | `react-native-iap` or **RevenueCat** (recommended — handles receipts, subscriptions, analytics) |
| Push Notifications | APNs | FCM | Expo Notifications (abstracts both) |
| Maps | Mapbox iOS SDK | Mapbox Android SDK | `@rnmapbox/maps` (handles both) |
| Widgets | WidgetKit (SwiftUI) | App Widgets (Kotlin) | No abstraction — native code on each platform (Phase 2) |
| Offline Storage | SQLite | SQLite | `react-native-sqlite-storage` (same API) |
| Haptic Feedback | UIImpactFeedbackGenerator | Vibrator API | `react-native-haptic-feedback` |

### Location Permissions (Critical — #1 App Store Rejection Risk)

**Phase 0: Foreground only.** The movement tracker runs while the app is open. This avoids the hardest permission issues.

**iOS permissions:**
- `NSLocationWhenInUseUsageDescription`: "FitRealm tracks your movement to convert steps into in-game resources for your village."
- Request "When In Use" permission during the first movement session, NOT during onboarding (Apple rejects apps that request permissions before the user understands why)
- Do NOT request "Always" permission in Phase 0

**Android permissions:**
- `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` (precise GPS)
- Android 12+: user may grant "approximate only" — detect this and show a prompt explaining why precise location is needed for distance tracking
- Android 13+: `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` must be requested separately at runtime (not auto-granted)
- Battery optimization: show a one-time prompt linking to device settings if Doze mode is detected during a movement session

**Phase 2: Background location.**
- iOS: upgrade to "Always" permission with a clear in-app explainer. Apple requires a visible justification in the app AND in App Store review notes.
- Android: `ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION` — must be requested SEPARATELY from foreground location (Google Play policy). Show a dedicated explanation screen before the permission dialog.
- Both platforms: use `react-native-background-geolocation` which handles foreground service (Android) and background modes (iOS) correctly.

### In-App Purchase Strategy

**Use RevenueCat** (free up to $2,500/mo revenue) instead of raw `react-native-iap`. RevenueCat:
- Abstracts StoreKit (iOS) and Google Play Billing (Android) behind one API
- Handles receipt validation server-side (prevents jailbreak/root purchase fraud)
- Manages subscription lifecycle (renewals, cancellations, grace periods)
- Provides revenue analytics dashboard
- Handles the App Store's "Restore Purchases" requirement automatically

**Revenue split awareness:**
- Apple: 30% cut (15% if enrolled in Small Business Program — under $1M/year revenue)
- Google: 15% on first $1M, then 30%
- Price gems/packs to account for this. A $4.99 Supporter Pack nets ~$4.24 (Apple SBP) or ~$4.24 (Google)
- Subscription prices must be set per-platform in App Store Connect and Google Play Console

**Required IAP implementation details:**
- "Restore Purchases" button in Settings (Apple REQUIRES this — rejection without it)
- Subscription management link in Settings (both platforms require easy cancellation access)
- Receipt validation via RevenueCat server (never trust client-side purchase verification)
- Gem balance stored server-side in Supabase (not on-device) to prevent manipulation

### Push Notification Permissions

**iOS:**
- Request notification permission after the player completes their first movement session (not during onboarding)
- Support provisional notifications (iOS 12+) for quiet delivery initially
- Notification categories for actionable notifications: "Rally Back" button on faction events, "Start Moving" on decay warnings

**Android:**
- Android 12 and below: notifications granted by default
- Android 13+: `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` must be requested at runtime — do this after first movement session
- Create notification channels: "Village Alerts" (high priority), "Faction Activity" (default), "Events & Quests" (default), "Reminders" (low priority)
- Users can disable individual channels in system settings — respect this

### Platform-Specific UI Requirements

**Both platforms:**
- Use `react-native-safe-area-context` for all screens (handles notch, Dynamic Island, Android cutouts)
- Bottom tab navigation (React Navigation bottom tabs) — standard on both platforms
- `react-native-haptic-feedback` for satisfying tactile responses: allocation confirmed, building built, achievement unlocked, rally sent

**iOS-specific:**
- Swipe-to-go-back enabled by default (React Navigation handles this)
- Large title headers on main screens (iOS convention)
- SF Symbols for system icons where appropriate
- Dynamic Island live activity for active movement sessions (Phase 3)

**Android-specific:**
- Hardware back button handling on all screens (React Navigation handles this)
- Material Design 3 ripple effects on buttons
- Edge-to-edge display support (Android 15+)
- Predictive back gesture support

### Build & Deployment

**Development:**
- Test on both platforms for EVERY feature before merging
- iOS: Xcode + iOS Simulator (requires Mac)
- Android: Android Studio + emulator (any OS)
- Physical device testing required for: GPS tracking, HealthKit/Health Connect, push notifications, haptics

**CI/CD (Phase 1):**
- Use **EAS Build** (Expo Application Services) for cloud builds — builds iOS without a Mac in CI
- Or: GitHub Actions + Fastlane for more control
- Separate build configs: development, staging, production

**Signing & Certificates:**
- iOS: Apple Developer Program ($99/year). Provisioning profiles, signing certificates, App Store Connect setup.
- Android: Generate a keystore for signing. Store securely — losing it means you can't update the app. Upload signing key to Google Play App Signing (recommended).

**Distribution:**
- iOS: TestFlight for beta → App Store for production
- Android: Internal Testing Track → Closed Testing → Production on Google Play
- Both platforms can be submitted simultaneously

### Android Device Fragmentation

**GPS accuracy:**
- Android GPS accuracy varies wildly across devices and manufacturers
- The Kalman filter + 20m accuracy threshold handles most of this
- Cheap devices may have GPS drift of 50m+ — consider a 30m threshold as a fallback config in `game_config`

**Battery optimization (Android-specific problem):**
- Samsung, Xiaomi, Huawei, OnePlus, and Oppo all have aggressive battery optimization that kills background processes
- `react-native-background-geolocation` handles most cases, but some devices require manual whitelisting
- On first movement session, detect the device manufacturer. If it's a known aggressive OEM, show a one-time guide: "To ensure accurate tracking, please disable battery optimization for FitRealm" with a deep link to the relevant settings page
- Use the `dontkillmyapp.com` API/database for manufacturer-specific instructions
- This is a KNOWN pain point for every fitness app on Android — it's not solvable in code alone, but good UX around it minimizes user frustration

