## Onboarding Design (First 5 Minutes + First 7 Days)

Onboarding is the single highest-impact feature for retention. If a player doesn't understand the core loop and feel emotionally invested within the first session, they won't come back. Design every step to be action-first — teach by doing, not explaining.

### First Session (5 minutes)

**Step 1 — Splash + Hook (30 seconds)**
- Animated splash: a small village in a fantasy landscape, resources depleting
- Single line of text: "Your village needs you. Every step you take keeps it alive."
- Button: "Build My Village →"

**Step 2 — Sign In (30 seconds)**
- Google or Apple sign-in via Supabase Auth
- No email/password option in Phase 1 (reduces friction)

**Step 3 — Name & Place Your Village (60 seconds)**
- "Name your village" text input (default suggestion generated: "Thornhaven", "Mistwood", etc.)
- Full world Mapbox map: "Tap anywhere to place your village"
- Helper text: "This is your kingdom's home — choose anywhere on Earth"
- Optional: "Use my current location" button
- Confirm placement → brief animation of village being built

**Step 4 — The First Crisis (60 seconds)**
- Immediately after village placement, a narrative event triggers:
  - "⚠️ Your villagers are hungry! They need food to survive the night."
  - Resource meters appear — Food is at 30/100 (visually urgent, yellow/orange)
  - "Hunt for food by walking. Any distance counts."
  - Big button: "Start Moving →" (launches the movement tracker)
- The player walks even 0.1 miles (across the room, down the hallway — anything)
- On stopping: "You hunted successfully! +50 Food 🎉"
- Food meter fills to 80. Village shows happy villagers. Celebration animation.
- This completes the FULL core loop in under 2 minutes: move → bank miles → auto-allocate → village improves

**Step 5 — Tutorial Wrap (30 seconds)**
- Quick overlay explaining: "Your village has 4 needs: Food, Medicine, Wood, Morale"
- "Move every day to keep your village alive and growing"
- "You have a 24-hour grace period — no decay until tomorrow"
- Button: "Enter My Village →" — drops into the Home screen

### First 7 Days — Onboarding Quest Chain

A guided quest chain that teaches one mechanic per day. Each quest auto-generates the morning after the previous one is completed. Rewards are tuned to be generous so new players feel powerful early.

| Day | Quest Name | Teaches | Task | Reward |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | "Feed Your People" | Core movement → resource loop | Walk/move any distance | +50 Food, +10 Gems |
| 2 | "Stock the Supplies" | Allocate screen + choosing | Bank 0.5 mi, then allocate to Medicine or Wood | +30 to chosen resource, +10 Gems |
| 3 | "Explore Your Land" | Map + fog of war | Allocate 1 mile to Scout | 4 hex tiles revealed, +10 Gems |
| 4 | "Find Your Allies" | Factions | Join or create a faction | +20 Morale, +15 Gems, faction intro |
| 5 | "Rally Your Friends" | Rally system | Give 2 Rallies to faction members | +10 Morale, +10 Gems |
| 6 | "Rest & Recover" | Rest Day mechanic | Declare a Rest Day | +10 Morale, streak preserved, +10 Gems |
| 7 | "The Road Ahead" | Streak + long-term hook | Complete any movement (streak now = 7 days) | Village garden blooms (first visual milestone), +25 Gems, "First Week" achievement badge |

After Day 7: onboarding chain ends, regular random quest system takes over. A push notification congratulates them: "Your village survived its first week! You're a true realm keeper. 🏰"

### Post-Onboarding Milestone Quests
After the 7-day chain, special milestone quests trigger at key moments to introduce advanced mechanics:

| Trigger | Quest | Teaches |
|---|---|---|
| Player has 5+ banked miles AND no buildings | "Lay the First Stone" | Building system — guided prompt to build their first building. Reward: +20 Stone bonus |
| Player builds first building | "The Village Grows" | Building upgrades — explains tiers, shows what Lv 2 unlocks. Reward: +10 Gems |
| Player reaches 20 total miles banked (lifetime) | "Beyond the Horizon" | Expedition system — explains how travel triggers expeditions. Reward: +15 Gems |
| Player's faction completes first weekly quest | "Strength in Numbers" | Faction quest rewards + contributing miles. Reward: +20 Gems |
| Player earns 100 total Gems | "The Gem Economy" | Gem Shop — explains what gems buy. Reward: 1 free Streak Shield |

These quests appear as special gold-bordered quest cards on the home screen. They don't expire (unlike random quests) and disappear once completed.

