| Envoy | Trigger a Faction Envoy event |
| Challenger | Win a 1v1 Friend Challenge |

- Each achievement awards a gem bonus (10–100 gems depending on difficulty)
- Rare/hard achievements display with a glow effect on the profile

### E9. Onboarding Quest Chain (Phase 1)
**See "Onboarding Design" section above.** This is the guided 7-day quest sequence that teaches every mechanic through play, not text. Integrated into Phase 1 as a critical retention feature.

### E10. Village Chronicle — Progress Journal (Phase 1)
**Inspired by:** Zombies, Run! mission log, RPG quest journals
**Psychological driver:** Narrative identity — people stay engaged when they can look back and see a meaningful story of their effort.

- An auto-generated timeline of the player's journey, written in RPG narrative style
- Entries are created automatically on major events:
  - "Day 1 — The village of Thornhaven was founded in the misty hills of northern England."
  - "Day 7 — The first garden bloomed. The villagers celebrated."
  - "Day 14 — A great expedition to Chicago revealed ancient ruins in the western territories."
  - "Day 30 — The village walls were erected. Thornhaven stands strong."
  - "Day 45 — ShadowWalker received 50 rallies from allies. The realm takes notice."
- Players can add their own notes to chronicle entries (optional)
- The Chronicle is a scrollable timeline view accessible from the Profile tab
- Sharing: players can share a Chronicle entry as an image card (for social media) — generates a styled card with the entry text and a mini village illustration

### E11. Friend Challenges — 1v1 Competition (Phase 2)
**Inspired by:** Strava head-to-head segments, Apple Watch activity sharing competitions
**Psychological driver:** Direct competition + accountability — challenging a specific person is more motivating than a leaderboard of strangers.

- Any player can challenge one friend (must be in same faction or mutual follow) to a 1v1
- Challenge types:
  - **Distance Duel**: "Who can bank more miles this week?"
  - **Streak Standoff**: "Who can maintain their streak longer starting now?"
  - **Quest Race**: "Who can complete more random quests in 5 days?"
- Duration: 3, 5, or 7 days (challenger picks)
- Both players see a live comparison card on their home screen during the challenge
- Winner gets: +30 Gems, a temporary trophy icon on their profile for 7 days
- Loser gets: a funny cosmetic on their village for 24 hours (white surrender flag, sleeping villagers, etc.) — lighthearted, never mean
- Both players get a participation gem bonus (+10 Gems) regardless of outcome — encouraging people to accept challenges
- Max 1 active challenge at a time (to prevent notification fatigue)

### E12. Comeback Mechanic — "Return of the Wanderer" (Phase 1)
**Inspired by:** Duolingo's streak repair + mobile game lapsed-player campaigns
**Psychological driver:** Reducing re-entry friction — the #1 reason lapsed users don't return is feeling too far behind.

- Triggers when a player returns after 3+ days of inactivity
- Instead of showing a ruined village with guilt, show a **welcoming narrative**:
  - "The Wanderer returns! Your village has been waiting for you."
  - "Your people kept the fires burning, but they need your leadership."
- **Comeback Quest Chain** (3 quests over 3 days):
  - Quest 1: "Walk any distance to relight the village beacon" → Restores village from Ruined state + sets all resources to 40/100
  - Quest 2: "Bank 0.5 miles to restock supplies" → +20 to all resources + streak restarts at Day 1
  - Quest 3: "Rally 2 faction members to announce your return" → +30 Morale + "Wanderer Returns" event in faction feed
- On completing all 3: "Your village is restored! The realm celebrates your return. 🏰"
- Gem bonus: +25 Gems for completing the comeback chain
- Push notification after 3 days of inactivity: "Your village misses you. Come back and your people will celebrate! 🔥" (sent once, not repeatedly — never spam lapsed users)
- After 7 days of inactivity: one final notification: "The Wanderer's path awaits. Your village is ready when you are." Then silence — respect their choice.
- Realm Pass subscribers get an enhanced comeback with resources starting at 60/100 instead of 40/100

