## Phase Roadmap

### Phase 0 — Core Playable (Build This First)
The absolute minimum to have a playable game you can put on your phone and test. No engagement systems, no social features, no monetization. Just the core loop: **move → bank miles → allocate → village survives**. Target: 2–4 weeks of development.

#### Build Order (sequential — each step depends on the previous)

**Step 1: Scaffold + Auth (Days 1–2)**
- [ ] React Native bare workflow + TypeScript + ESLint + Prettier
- [ ] Verify builds and runs on both iOS Simulator AND Android Emulator
- [ ] Supabase project: create tables (profiles, villages, activities, allocations)
- [ ] Supabase Auth: Google Sign-In (both platforms) + Apple Sign-In (iOS — required for App Store if Google Sign-In is offered)
- [ ] Vercel project: deploy empty Express API
- [ ] Basic navigation structure (React Navigation) with safe area handling
- [ ] Set up RevenueCat project (free tier) — even though IAP is Phase 1, the SDK should be integrated early

**Step 2: Village Screen — Static (Days 3–5)**
- [ ] Village view UI: 4 resource meters (Food, Medicine, Wood, Morale) + Stone counter
- [ ] Mile Bank display
- [ ] Simple village illustration (static placeholder — no buildings yet)
- [ ] Connect to Supabase: load/save village state

**Step 3: Movement Tracker (Days 6–10)**
- [ ] Movement tracker screen: start/stop button, live GPS map (Mapbox), distance counter
- [ ] GPS point recording with Kalman filter + accuracy threshold
- [ ] Request location permission on first session start (not during onboarding): "When In Use" (iOS), ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION (Android)
- [ ] Handle Android 12+ approximate location grant — prompt for precise if approximate given
- [ ] Route recording (GeoJSON stored locally in SQLite)
- [ ] On movement end: calculate distance, apply movement type multiplier, add miles to bank
- [ ] Sync movement data to Supabase + route to Supabase Storage
- [ ] Manual entry screen: distance + duration input for treadmill/indoor
- [ ] Test GPS tracking on physical iPhone + physical Android device (emulator GPS is unreliable)

**Step 4: Allocate Miles (Days 11–13)**
- [ ] Allocate screen: list of options (Hunt Food, Gather Medicine, Chop Wood, Quarry Stone, Scout, Defend)
- [ ] Deduct miles from bank, add resources to village
- [ ] Verify: full core loop works end-to-end (move → bank → allocate → village resources update)

**Step 5: Village Decay (Days 14–15)**
- [ ] Vercel Cron: `/api/cron/village-decay` runs every 6 hours
- [ ] Decay logic: -8 per resource per tick, respects 24hr grace period
- [ ] Village state transitions: thriving → struggling (any resource <20) → ruined (all at 0 for 48hr)
- [ ] Verify: village decays when player is inactive, recovers when they allocate

**Step 6: Basic Map (Days 16–18)**
- [ ] Mapbox world map with custom fantasy style
- [ ] Village marker at player's chosen origin
- [ ] Fog of war: hex grid, tiles revealed by Scout allocations
