## App Store Strategy

#### App Name
"FitRealm" is the working title. Before launch, verify:
- Trademark search (USPTO for US, similar for other regions)
- App Store name availability (both iOS App Store and Google Play)
- Domain availability (fitrealm.app, fitrealmgame.com, etc.)
- Social media handle availability (@fitrealm)

#### Age Rating
- Target: **12+** (iOS) / **Everyone 10+** (Android)
- Multiplayer interaction is structured (no free-text messaging), which avoids a higher rating
- No violence, gambling, or mature content
- Health/fitness data access requires disclosure in App Store review

#### App Store Review Considerations
- **HealthKit usage**: Apple requires a clear description of why health data is accessed. Description: "FitRealm reads workout data (distance, duration) to convert your real-world movement into in-game resources."
- **Location usage**: Must explain background location access if used. Phase 0: foreground only = simpler review. Phase 2: background = needs strong justification string.
- **IAP**: All gem packs and Supporter Pack must use Apple/Google IAP — no external payment links.
- **Subscription**: Realm Pass must follow App Store subscription guidelines (free trial option, easy cancellation, restore purchases button).

#### Beta Testing Plan
- **Phase 0 beta**: TestFlight (iOS) + Google Play Internal Testing (Android). 10–20 friends/family testers.
- **Phase 1 beta**: Expand to 50–100 testers via TestFlight public link + Play Store closed testing track.
- **Soft launch**: Consider launching in a single smaller market (e.g. Canada, Australia) before worldwide release to catch issues at scale.
- Feedback collection: in-app feedback button (Phase 1) → sends to a Supabase `feedback` table or a simple Google Form.

