## Audio Design

Sound and music are Phase 2 polish — the app ships silent in Phase 0/1 with only system notification sounds. But the audio direction is defined here so it's consistent when added.

#### Audio Philosophy
FitRealm's audio should feel like a cozy medieval world — warm, ambient, never intrusive. Players will often use the app while listening to their own music or podcasts during movement, so game audio must never fight for attention.

#### Sound Effects (Phase 2)
| Event | Sound | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Allocation confirmed | Soft coin/resource gathering chime | Short, satisfying, like a chest opening |
| Building constructed | Hammer + wood construction sound | Brief, celebratory |
| Building upgraded | Deeper construction + fanfare | Slightly grander than Lv 1 |
| Achievement unlocked | Brass horn flourish | Distinct, rewarding, Zelda-chest-open energy |
| Rally received | Soft shield tap + crowd murmur | Subtle — shouldn't interrupt anything |
| Streak milestone | Rising tone sequence | Gets more elaborate at higher milestones |
| Random quest appeared | Scroll unfurling + light bell | Attention-getting but not alarming |
| Hex tile revealed | Shimmer/sparkle sweep | Satisfying scratch-off feel |
| Rare spawn discovered | Magical chime + glow sound | Special, immediately recognizable |
| Village entering Ruined state | Low ambient wind + distant bell | Somber but hopeful, not punishing |
| Comeback quest completed | Full orchestral swell (short) | Heroic, triumphant |

#### Background Music (Phase 2)
- Village scene: gentle medieval lute/flute ambient loop (~2 min, seamless loop)
- World map: slightly more adventurous ambient — light percussion + strings
- Movement tracker: NO music by default (player is likely listening to their own). Optional toggle.
- Music volume independent of SFX volume
- Master mute toggle respects device silent mode

#### Audio Implementation
- Use `expo-av` or `react-native-sound` for SFX
- All audio files bundled with the app (small MP3s, <100KB each)
- Global audio settings in Profile → Settings: Master Volume, SFX Volume, Music Volume, Music On/Off
- Respect device silent/vibrate mode — never play audio when phone is silenced

